Attention Football Reserved Seat holders:

Reserved seats will not be available during the 2020 football season. Last year's seat holders will have the option to keep seats for the 2021 season. We are sorry for any inconvenience this may cause. With the uncertainty of the times, ESD feels this is the best solution for this season. Gates will be open at 5:30 p.m. on game day. No seats may be saved in the stadium. Any items placed in the stadium prior to 5:30 p.m on game day will be removed.

As of today (August 20, 2020) and in accordance with the Executive Order No. 1518, each student participant will be allowed 2 guests. All tickets will be pre-sold! Each participant may only purchase 2 tickets.Only participants will be allowed to purchase tickets. Date and time of pre-sale will be announced. No tickets will be sold at the gate.

Thank you in advance for your support.

post_text:
We have had an awesome first day with our A-K learners at ESD! We cannot say thank you enough to our parents and students for such a phenomenal start! We cannot wait to see our students (last name L-Z) tomorrow!

In his press conference today, Governor Reeves announced a new Executive Order that will mandate masks in all public places, including schools. Just a reminder that the school district has ordered a cloth mask for each student. In addition, each school bus, classroom and office has disposable masks available for students in need. Students are welcome to wear their own masks as long as they do not contain disruptive language or images.

It's a great day to be a Bulldog!

#WhateverItTakes #itsgotime

For the 2020-21 school year, the Mississippi State Auditor's Office has waived proof of residency requirements for returning students who do NOT have a change of address for the 2020-21 school year.

Parents of returning students whose address has NOT changed since the previous school year may complete the registration process by printing this form and returning to your child‚Äôs office. This form may be e-mailed, faxed, or dropped off by the office anytime between 8:00 am and 3:00 pm (Mon - Thurs).

Registration Information letter and the verification form can be located on the school website. IF you are a NEW student or you have a change in address, you must come to the school on July 27-29 to complete the registration process. Thank you for your support!

As we enter the new school year, let us introduce the new faces to the Bulldog family.

CENSUS UPDATE:

As of June 11, the national response rate was 60.9%, and Mississippi‚Äôs response rate was 56.1%.
**Clarke County had a response rate of 50.3%.
**Enterprise has a response rate of 41.9%.

It is important that you complete the 2020 Census. Households can respond to the 2020 Census here: https://my2020census.gov/.

Remember, it‚Äôs quick and easy to respond, and all responses are safe, secure, and confidential. People may also return their paper questionnaire or respond by telephone at 1-844-330-2020 (English) or 1-844-468-2020 (Spanish).

The Census Bureau will continue its communications campaign through October 2020 ‚Äî the end of 2020 Census data collection operations.

Thank you in advance for those in our Bulldog community who have completed the Census! Please do your part!!!! Go Bulldogs!

CLASS OF 2020 - GRADUATION
Tuesday, JUNE 23, 2020
EMS GYMNASIUM

Graduates A-L (7:00)
Graduates M-Z (8:15)

Graduation for seniors with the last name beginning A-L will begin at 7:00 pm.
Doors will open to the EMS Gymnasium at 6:30 pm.

Graduation for seniors with the last name beginning M-Z will begin at 8:15 pm.

Tickets will be collected upon entry to the gym and can only be used for one ceremony

Seniors received more information this morning at practice! Parents please ask your senior for the note!

The live stream link will be posted later this evening for those not able to attend!

Thank you for your support of ESD and the Class of 2020!

Clarke County Health Department will be holding Back to School Immunization Clinics on June 18th, July 21st, and July 28th. All clinics will be held from 8am-4pm at the Clarke County Health Department located at 426 West Donald Street in Quitman. post_text:
May 29, 2020

Enterprise School District sets physicals date

Enterprise School District will have physicals for all students planning to participate in Grades 7-12 athletics or activities. Physicals will be held on Friday, June 12, 2020 in the high school gym. Due to social distancing guidelines, the following schedule will be followed:

8 AM - 8:30 AM 7th and 8th Graders
8:30 AM - 9 AM 9th and 10th Graders
9 AM - 9:30 AM 11th and 12th Graders

ONLY students should leave vehicles to enter the gym for physicals.

Parents and students should park in the student parking lot at the high school.

The physicals are no charge to the student. Any student that does not get a physical on this date will be required to acquire their own physical prior to the start of official practice dates for their sport.

Parents need to print the physical form attached and fill out the top and sign. Students should bring with them on the date of physicals.

https://drive.google.com/file/d/1chJ8Ca9uvOWr7wmjDut0QJjRSEPnyNMv/view

post_text:
According to Newton‚Äôs 3rd Law of Motion, with every action, there is an equal and opposite reaction. With the action of Coach Weathers‚Äô retirement, Coach Brannan will be leaving the middle school and assuming duties as high school principal on July 1st. Also, Mrs. Jessica Guy has been promoted from her current position and will take on the role of middle school principal on July 1st.

Both of these individuals have huge shoes to fill; however, we are excited about the energy and passion they both possess and look forward to watching them lead our schools into the future. Congratulations Coach Brannan and Mrs. Guy!

post_text:
Only 13 spots remain for summer camp!

üó£ We are inviting any student currently in grade 3rd-6th to join our 2nd ANNUAL Y.E.S. SUMMER CAMP featuring Bloxels and Cue Robots. You can choose between 2 different courses: video game building or robotics.
Please send us your registration information to agoodman@esd.k12.ms.us. Be sure to include your child‚Äôs name, current grade level, t-shirt size, parent cell phone number, and which session your child is attending (morning or afternoon/ robotics or video game). There are limited spots for each class, so registration will close when all spots have been filled. You will get an email response confirming your registration. Your camp fee will be due when you arrive on the first day of camp (June 15th). See the attached registration form for more information. We are so excited!

üó£ We are inviting any student currently in grade 3rd-6th to join our 2nd ANNUAL Y.E.S. SUMMER CAMP featuring Bloxels and Cue Robots. You can choose between 2 different courses: video game building or robotics.
Please send us your registration information to agoodman@esd.k12.ms.us. Be sure to include your child‚Äôs name, current grade level, t-shirt size, parent cell phone number, and which session your child is attending (morning or afternoon/ robotics or video game). There are limited spots for each class, so registration will close when all spots have been filled. You will get an email response confirming your registration. Your camp fee will be due when you arrive on the first day of camp (June 15th). See the attached registration form for more information. We are so excited!

As school closures continue and as the state develops plans to direct resources to the areas of greatest need, the Mississippi Department of Education has prepared a brief survey for districts to circulate. The survey focuses on devices at home, home internet access, and the quality/reliability of that connection.

Please take a few minutes and complete the survey.

https://cspr.mde.k12.ms.us/TakeSurvey.aspx?SurveyID=mlK09726#

A word from Coach Sollie:

Boys high school tryouts for incoming 9-12 graders tentatively will be Saturday morning June 6 from 9:30-11 at the high school gym. This of course pending the go ahead on June 1 to resume activities. Information about junior high tryouts, high school workouts and practices, etc will come closer to time.

I encourage players to start working on their game again and getting back in shape during the month of May so we can hit the ground running. As always stay safe, and look forward to seeing everyone again!

Enterprise School District
April 14, 2020 School Closure Update

In accordance with state guidance from Governor Tate Reeves, Enterprise School District will remain closed for the rest of the school year. Please stay tuned for additional information about how ESD will continue to offer remote and at home learning. Please be patient and continue to stay the course over the next few days. Our grab-and-go meal service will continue through this week. A breakfast and lunch may be picked up for your child in the loop in front of the high school from 11:00am to noon each day.

#whateverittakes (the Governor quoted our motto in his press conference - we way ahead of you Governor!)

Mrs. Prater (10th grade English teacher) wants to challenge each and every Bulldog learner in the district during this distant learning time. Bulldogs of ALL ages: Don't let the 10th graders out work you!

This is the message Mrs. Prater sent to her students today....

As of today, I have talked to and had some (if not all work) turned in by this amazing Sophomore class. üëè

Parents, you have been instrumental in helping me to set up communication during this difficult time. I think the success of these students clearly comes from the examples set by you! Thank you!

Students, I'm so humbled by your efforts! Continue to show this kind of dedication, and you will go far. This is one of the most amazing experiences of my teaching career. Thank you! I love and miss you all!
#SophomoreStrong!üëèüëèüíï
